        <name>10.3.4.2 Hyperbolic function of a complex number</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Express &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(z={@exp@}(a+ib)\)&lt;/span&gt; in Cartesian form:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\(z=\quad\)[[input:ans1]][[validation:ans1]] \(\quad+\quad\) [[input:ans2]][[validation:ans2]]\(\ \ i\)&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; [[feedback:prt1]]&amp;nbsp; [[feedback:prt2]]&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hint:&lt;/strong&gt; the imaginary unit, \(i\), should not appear in your final expressions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Therefore find the real and imaginary parts of \(z = {@exp@}(1 + {@im@}i)\). Express your answers in decimal form, rounding to 3 decimal places if necessary:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt; \(\text{Re}(z)=\quad\)[[input:ans3]][[validation:ans3]][[feedback:prt3]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; \(\text{Im}(z)=\quad\)[[input:ans4]][[validation:ans4]][[feedback:prt4]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;We use the hyperbolic sum-angle identity, followed by Osborne's rule:\[{@expr[1]@}(a+ib) \equiv {@expr[1]@}(a)\cosh(ib) +{@expr[6]@}(a)\sinh(ib) \equiv {@ta1@} + i\,{@ta2@}.\]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We then plug in \(a=1\) and \(b={@im@}\) to get:\[{@expr[1]@}(1+{@im@}i) = {@ta3@} + {@ta4@}i.\]&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
